'''Sasazuka Kofun''' (笹塚古墳) is a {{ill|keyhole-shaped kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Higashiya-machi, {{ill|Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Tochigi Prefecture. This article also covers the '''Higashiya Kofun Cluster''', with Sasazuka Kofun as its primary mound.

== Overview ==
Sasazuka Kofun is one of the largest keyhole-shaped kofun in Tochigi Prefecture, measuring 100 meters in total length. The rear circular section has a diameter of 63 meters and a height of 10.5 meters, while the front rectangular section measures 48 meters wide and 8.5 meters high. A shield-shaped moat likely surrounded the mound, based on its peripheral layout. The summit of the rear circular section has been flattened and now hosts a Yakushi-dō (hall dedicated to Yakushi Buddha). Evidence of tomb robbery is visible on the southern side of the Yakushi-dō, and fragments of {{ill|cylindrical haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were discovered atop the mound.

In 2006 (Heisei 18), the {{ill|Utsunomiya City Board of Education|ja|宇都宮市教育委員会|qq=draft|qq=draft}} conducted an excavation, confirming a double moat and a three-tiered mound structure. Traces of {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺石|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were also identified. Based on the mound's type, it is estimated to have been constructed in the mid-5th century, during the middle {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

burial goods recovered from the site include:
* {{ill|Cylindrical haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Morning glory-shaped haniwa|ja|朝顔形埴輪|1=Morning glory-shaped haniwa|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

On June 30, 1956 (Showa 31), Sasazuka Kofun, along with {{ill|Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, was Historic Site1 a Tochigi Prefecture Historic Site.

== Surrounding Environment ==
Sasazuka Kofun is situated on the eastern bank of the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tone River System)|ja|田川 (利根川水系)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in southern Utsunomiya. Nearby are several other Kofuns, including Tsurumai-zuka Kofun (a destroyed round kofun), Matsuno-zuka Kofun, Futago-zuka Kofun (with its front section destroyed), Gongen-zuka Kofun, Gongen-zuka Kita Kofun, Kuruma-zuka Kofun, and the Hara Kofun Cluster, collectively typeing the Higashiya Kofun Cluster.

== Higashiya Kofun Cluster ==
The '''Higashiya Kofun Cluster''' is located in Higashiya-machi, Utsunomiya City, Tochigi Prefecture. Sasazuka Kofun is considered the primary mound, with 11 smaller mounds located within a 500-meter radius.

This cluster is believed to represent the graves of regional elites from the area, succeeding the {{ill|Mobara Kofun Cluster|ja|茂原古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the western bank of the Tagawa River.

=== Tsurumai-zuka Kofun ===
Tsurumai-zuka Kofun is a round mound located south of Sasazuka Kofun. Its diameter exceeds 50 meters, with a height of approximately 6 meters. burial goods include fragments of iron hoes and iron arrowheads. The moat remains suggest it was constructed after Sasazuka Kofun.

=== Futago-zuka Kofun ===
Futago-zuka Kofun is a keyhole-shaped kofun north of Sasazuka Kofun. Its front section has been destroyed, leaving only the rear circular section with a diameter of about 20 meters and a height of 4 meters. No haniwa have been found.

=== Gongen-zuka Kofun ===
Gongen-zuka Kofun is a round mound southeast of Sasazuka Kofun, measuring 30 meters in diameter and 5 meters in height.

=== Gongen-zuka Kita Kofun ===
Gongen-zuka Kita Kofun is a small round mound located north of Gongen-zuka Kofun.

=== Matsuno-zuka Kofun ===
Matsuno-zuka Kofun is a scallop-shaped keyhole mound southwest of Sasazuka Kofun. The mound's periphery has been eroded by rice fields, and its estimated diameter and type are approximations.

=== Kuruma-zuka Kofun Cluster ===
Kuruma-zuka Kofun is a round mound located southeast of Sasazuka Kofun, within a wooded area. It has a diameter of about 35 meters and a height of approximately 6 meters. Together with four nearby round mounds, it types the Kuruma-zuka Kofun Cluster.

=== Hara Kofun Cluster ===
The Hara Kofun Cluster is located east of Sasazuka Kofun and consists of two round mounds, which are currently used as graveyards.

== Access ==
'''By Bus'''
* From {{ill|Utsunomiya Station|ja|宇都宮駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (JR):
** Take the {{ill|Kantō Bus|ja|関東自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Kamimikawa Line for approximately 20 minutes. Get off at "Higashiya" and walk 3 minutes.

'''By Car'''
* From the National Route 121 ({{ill|Utsunomiya Ring Road|ja|宇都宮環状道路|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) Shitayokota Intersection, drive south for 3 minutes along Kamimikawa Highway (Prefectural Route 35). The site is located on the east side of the road.

